formance XML streaming and parser reuse. It also improves handling of non-text XML infosets and namespace processing for JAXB and Metro use cases.\",\nmetadata/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/index.json:36:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/jvnet/staxex/stax-ex/$version$/stax-ex-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/index.json:37:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/javaee/metro-stax-ex\",\nmetadata/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/index.json:38:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/javaee/metro-stax-ex/tree/$version$/stax-ex/src/test\",\nmetadata/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/index.json:39:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/jvnet/staxex/stax-ex/$version$/stax-ex-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jvnet.staxex/stax-ex/index.json:40:    \"description\" : \"stax-ex provides extensions to the JSR-173 StAX API for handling binary and streaming XML content in Java. It adds XMLStreamReader and XMLStreamWriter support that enables efficient access to data such as base64-backed content without unnecessary copying.\",\nmetadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/index.json:11:    \"source-code-url\": \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8/ehcache-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/index.json:12:    \"repository-url\": \"https://github.com/ehcache/ehcache3\",\nmetadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/index.json:13:    \"test-code-url\": \"https://github.com/ehcache/ehcache3/tree/v3.10.8/integration-test/src/test\",\nmetadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/index.json:14:    \"documentation-url\": \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8/ehcache-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/index.json:15:    \"description\": \"Ehcache is an open source, standards-based Java cache that improves performance, reduces database load, and simplifies scalability. It supports both the Ehcache API and the JSR-107 cache API, with configurations ranging from in-process caches to larger tiered deployments.\"\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-api/index.json:6:    \"source-code-url\": \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/opencensus/opencensus-api/$version$/opencensus-api-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-api/index.json:7:    \"repository-url\": \"https://github.com/census-instrumentation/opencensus-java\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-api/index.json:8:    \"test-code-url\": \"https://github.com/census-instrumentation/opencensus-java/tree/v$version$/api/src/test\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-api/index.json:9:    \"documentation-url\": \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/opencensus/opencensus-api/$version$/opencensus-api-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-api/index.json:10:    \"description\": \"OpenCensus API provides Java APIs for collecting application metrics, distributed traces, and tags. It lets libraries and applications record telemetry data that can be exported by OpenCensus implementations.\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/$version$/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/census-instrumentation/opencensus-java\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/census-instrumentation/opencensus-java/tree/v$version$/contrib/grpc_util/src/test\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/$version$/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.opencensus/opencensus-contrib-grpc-util/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"OpenCensus gRPC Util provides Java utilities for adding trace instrumentation around gRPC usage. This artifact includes helpers for mapping gRPC status values to OpenCensus trace status values.\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-exceptions/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/playframework/play-exceptions/$version$/play-exceptions-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-exceptions/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/playframework/playframework\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-exceptions/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"N/A\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-exceptions/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/playframework/play-exceptions/$version$/play-exceptions-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-exceptions/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Play Exceptions provides the core Play Framework exception types used to carry structured error details such as titles, descriptions, source locations, attachments, and rich HTML descriptions. It supports Play's developer error reporting by exposing reusable exception classes that can identify relevant source lines and attach additional diagnostic content.\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-build-link/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/playframework/play-build-link/$version$/play-build-link-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-build-link/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/playframework/playframework\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-build-link/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"N/A\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-build-link/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/playframework/play-build-link/$version$/play-build-link-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.playframework/play-build-link/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Play Build Link defines the Java interfaces used by the Play build plugin to communicate with an embedded Play server during development. It supports application reloading, source lookup for error reporting, project path discovery, forced reloads, and build-provided settings while avoiding Scala-version coupling between the plugin and server.\",\nmetadata/org.datanucleus/javax.jdo/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/datanucleus/javax.jdo/$version$/javax.jdo-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.datanucleus/javax.jdo/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/datanucleus/javax.jdo\",\nmetadata/org.datanucleus/javax.jdo/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/datanucleus/javax.jdo/tree/javax.jdo-$version$/src/test\",\nmetadata/org.datanucleus/javax.jdo/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/datanucleus/javax.jdo/$version$/javax.jdo-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.datanucleus/javax.jdo/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Java Data Objects (JDO) API defines standard interfaces and annotations for Java object persistence. This artifact provides the JDO 3.2 API classes used by applications and persistence providers to model, query, and manage persistent Java objects.\",\nmetadata/com.github.mwiede/jsch/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/github/mwiede/jsch/$version$/jsch-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/com.github.mwiede/jsch/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/mwiede/jsch\",\nmetadata/com.github.mwiede/jsch/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/mwiede/jsch/tree/jsch-$version$/src/test\",\nmetadata/com.github.mwiede/jsch/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/github/mwiede/jsch/$version$/jsch-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/com.github.mwiede/jsch/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"JSch is a pure Java implementation of the SSH2 protocol. It provides client-side APIs for SSH sessions and related operations such as secure file transfer, port forwarding, and command execution.\",\nmetadata/io.zipkin.zipkin2/zipkin/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/zipkin/zipkin2/zipkin/$version$/zipkin-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.zipkin.zipkin2/zipkin/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin\",\nmetadata/io.zipkin.zipkin2/zipkin/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin/tree/$version$/zipkin-tests/src/test\",\nmetadata/io.zipkin.zipkin2/zipkin/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/zipkin/zipkin2/zipkin/$version$/zipkin-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.zipkin.zipkin2/zipkin/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Zipkin Core Library provides the core data model and codecs for representing and encoding distributed tracing spans. It includes APIs and utilities for traces, endpoints, annotations, dependency links, and query-related types used by Zipkin.\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/$version$/bcpkix-jdk15to18-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java/tree/r1rv77/pkix/src/test\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/$version$/bcpkix-jdk15to18-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Provides Bouncy Castle Java APIs for PKIX, CMS, PKCS, EAC, TSP, CMP, CRMF, OCSP, and certificate generation. It targets JDK 1.5 through JDK 1.8 and is typically used alongside a JCE/JCA provider such as Bouncy Castle's cryptography provide